                            <comment id="115591" author="rwinch" created="Wed, 13 May 2015 06:32:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report. We cannot write every time something is written to the response as this would not perform. This is likely due to the fact that if the buffer hits the content length it also flushes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="115597" author="xtof" created="Wed, 13 May 2015 10:30:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can we imagine to have just the first write that is checking if the context need to be saved?&lt;br/&gt;
this is how i implemented it indeed, leveraging the isContextSaved() to not do it twice, but at least i&apos;m doing it at last resort no later than the response is starting to be send&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="117615" author="rwinch" created="Tue, 14 Jul 2015 13:12:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=Xtof&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;Xtof&quot;&gt;Christophe Dehaudt&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the additional input. Without a concrete example it is hard to know exactly what is causing your issue and how to properly fix it. I do see that if the response is committed due to the body size reaching the content-length we are not saving the SecurityContext. I have pushed these changes out to master and 3.2.x and am resolving this issue for now.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you could give the change a try we can find out if this resolves the issue for you. If it does not resolve the issue, we can open a new issue and I will need a sample to reproduce the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For instructions on using Maven with your latest SNAPSHOT, please refer to the &lt;a href=&quot;http://docs.spring.io/spring-security/site/docs/3.2.x-SNAPSHOT/reference/htmlsingle/#maven&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;reference documentation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
